# Plan: Fix Hover Action Overlap Platform-Wide

## Problem Summary

The Notes page has overlapping hover actions that make the note title unreadable. When hovering over a note card, action buttons (Download, PDF Export, Star, Pin, Delete) positioned at `absolute top-2 right-8` overlap with the note title "November 28, 2025".

This is a symptom of a platform-wide issue affecting 24 files with hover actions. Three files have high overlap risk, three have medium risk.

## Root Cause

**Immediate cause:** Absolute positioned actions at `top-2 right-8` compete with:
- Static indicators (Star, Pin) at `top-2 right-2`
- Title text with only `pr-6` padding (insufficient for 5 buttons × 24px = 120px)

**Systemic cause:** No standard pattern for hover actions that prevents overlap while avoiding layout shift.

## Proposed Solution

### Core Pattern: Reserved Action Zone with Flexbox

Replace absolute positioning with flex-based layout that reserves space for actions:

**Key Principles:**
1. **Header Row:** Title and actions in same flex container
2. **Title Flexibility:** `flex-1 min-w-0` allows truncation before overlap
3. **Fixed Action Width:** `shrink-0` + fixed width (140px) prevents collapse
4. **Opacity Transition:** Actions occupy space via `opacity-0`, preventing shift
5. **Logical Grouping:** Static indicators and hover actions separated clearly

**Example:**
```tsx
<div className="flex items-start gap-2 min-h-[24px]">
  {/* Title: grows, truncates when constrained */}
  <h4 className="font-medium flex-1 truncate min-w-0">
    {note.title}
  </h4>

  {/* Reserved action zone: always 140px wide */}
  <div className="flex items-center gap-1 shrink-0" style={{ width: '140px' }}>
    {/* Static indicators (always visible) */}
    <div className="flex gap-1 ml-auto">
      {note.isFavorite && <Star className="w-4 h-4" />}
      {note.isPinned && <Pin className="w-4 h-4" />}
    </div>

    {/* Hover actions (invisible but occupy space) */}
    <div className="flex gap-1 opacity-0 group-hover:opacity-100">
      {/* 5 buttons */}
    </div>
  </div>
</div>
```

**Advantages:**
- ✅ Zero overlap (flexbox enforces boundaries)
- ✅ No layout shift (actions always occupy space)
- ✅ Responsive (title truncates gracefully)
- ✅ Predictable (fixed action width)
- ✅ Maintainable (standard flex patterns)

**Tradeoffs:**
- ⚠️ Cards ~140px wider (acceptable for readability)
- ⚠️ Titles truncate earlier (but readable vs. overlapped)

